snippet.textDisplay: I love Sylvester and i've loved watching your channel for the past year now. I first found Sylvester through a tik tok video that someone re-posted a video blip in! This is probably really random (maybe not?) but it made me really happy to hear the ending comments about bipolar disorder. While I don't have bipolar disorder myself, I have BPD. I used to have a misdiagnosis for rapid cycling bipolar disorder that eventually was amended. But it's always a nice moment to hear others struggle too, especially people who I watch on youtube. Not that struggling itself is a good thing, but it makes everything feel a little more normal. Either way, I just want to say I hope all is well and I hope you have a happy new year! And if you don't that's okay too. Your content is so funny, and I love watching! I always look forward to your videos, regardless of how long or short the period is between new videos. You have my full support! <3

snippet.textDisplay: Love your videos and sense of humor! I've watched them back to back for hours sometimes to avoid reality (depression, anxiety, ADHD, and PTSD). They make the world seem brighter plus, I love cats. I'm seeing a counselor and medication provider and have for a few years. I hope you are seeking treatment too. Not to sound preachy and some days I hate it, but my medications make my mental health issues seem like a bump in the road as opposed to a mountain. It also makes the down times shorter and less bleak, as does seeing my counselor twice a month. At first I felt like I was bitching and feeling sorry for myself, which I didn't like, but then I started to ubderstand feelings are normal, everyone has them, and the counseling is for tools to help myself, not for someone else to fix me. I feel more empowered now, and less crippled by my illness. Also, being open and honest with friends really helped. I don't feel alone, but yes sometimes I isolate when I need to catch my breath. I also have awesome friends who call me on my bullshit when I need it too. None of us are alone in this fight. Plus having my five fur kids around helps so much more than at first I realized. ❤❤❤❤❤
